The paper deals with visual relationship detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a natural language guided framework, which involves natural language processing techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The proposed method uses a recurrent neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also involves evaluating the proposed method's performance, which falls under the category of evaluation and experimentation, making cs.LG (Learning) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves predicting semantic connections between objects, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
